nhc_headline: ...DEPRESSION BECOMES TROPICAL STORM OCTAVE WELL TO THE SOUTH-SOUTHWEST OF BAJA CALIFORNIA...
summary: ...DEPRESSION BECOMES TROPICAL STORM OCTAVE WELL TO THE SOUTH-SOUTHWEST OF BAJA CALIFORNIA... As of 8:00 AM MST Tue Sep 30 the center of Octave was located near 9.9, -113.5 with movement NW at 5 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1004 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 40 mph.
